SCENARIO.RESTRICTION.LIVE_CHECK.DESC: Live checks can be defined in any reference system and check at runtime whether there is an overlap with a virtual wall. If this is the case, the current robot movement is stopped. So a slight intrusion into the area of a Virtual Wall is present and depends on the robot speed. To use Live Checks, they must be activated in the "Virtual Walls" component.
SCENARIO.RESTRICTION.TOOL_AREA.DESC: Tool areas are defined on the robot flange and calculate possible intersections with virtual walls before a movement is executed. If an overlap is detected, the movement is not executed. This makes it impossible to enter the area of the virtual walls. For tool areas to have an effect, at least one virtual wall must be defined in the system and the component “Virtual Walls” has to be installed.
SCENARIO.RESTRICTION.VIRTUAL_WALL.DESC: Virtual walls allow you to restrict the robot's workspace. Based on the tool areas and live checks you set, movement in this area is not possible. For Virtual Walls to have an effect, at least one tool area must be defined in the system and the component “Virtual Walls” has to be installed.

ZIMMER_DEVICE_MODE_DESC: Selects the desired operating mode of the gripper.
ZIMMER_PORT_OUT_OF_RANGE: No gripper connected on this IO-Port
ZIMMER_POSITION_TOLERANCE_DESC: Sets the position detection tolerance around the parameter 'Teach Position'. The width is applied to both sides of the teach position.
ZIMMER_SHIFT_POSITION_DESC: Sets the shift position which is used in some device modes. Shall be numerically larger than 'Base Position'.
ZIMMER_TEACH_POSITION_DESC: Sets the center detection position for the workpiece detection. Refer to the parameter 'Position Tolerance' to set a tolerance window.
ZIMMER_WORK_POSITION_DESC: Sets the innermost position. Shall be numerically larger than 'Base Position' and 'Shift Position'.
ZIMMER_WORKPIECE_NO_DESC: Selects the already stored workpiece data or selects the workpiece data in which the current process data will be stored.
ZIMMER.NO_DEVICE: Zimmer Gripper Component has no connected device. To configure a device go to the Component Manager and change the “Device Type” setting for the port your Zimmer Gripper is connected to.
TOUR.HEADING: Guided tours
TOUR.LIST.DESC: Start a tour to learn more about drag&bot's core features:
TOUR.WELCOME2: Take a guided tour to explore the software.
TOUR.WELCOME3: If you skip the tour now, you can start it any time by clicking the light bulb button on the home screen. You'll find this button throughout the software to get context related tips.
TOUR.BASIC.TITLE: drag&bot 101
TOUR.BASIC.WELCOME: Welcome to drag&bot! In this tour you will get a basic overview of the software.
TOUR.BASIC.NAVIGATION.TEXT: With the left sidebar you can navigate through the software.
TOUR.BASIC.HOME.TEXT: On the home screen you will get an overview of your robot system and have direct access to the most important functions.
TOUR.BASIC.LIBRARY.TEXT: Here you can find and manage your programs.
TOUR.BASIC.RUNVIEW.TEXT: The fully configurable HMI for the operator. Parameterize, execute and monitor programs.
TOUR.BASIC.OPERATORS_PANEL.TEXT: Control your hardware, e.g. move the robot or control the gripper.
TOUR.BASIC.ROBOT_SYSTEM.TEXT: Here you can configure your robot system, including your hardware components.
TOUR.BASIC.SCENARIO_DESIGNER.TEXT: Here you can adjust the robot environment to your needs.
TOUR.BASIC.TEAM.TEXT: Here you can manage your team accounts and add users with different permission levels (roles).
TOUR.BASIC.SUPPORT.TEXT: Here you find the link to our online documentation and video tutorials and a list of all guided tours.
TOUR.BASIC.ROBOT_STATUS.TEXT: Check the status of your robot system and robot at any time.
TOUR.BASIC.END: This was the "drag&bot 101" tour. You can find all tours at Menu/Help and throughout the product at each light bulb.
TOUR.LIBRARY.TABLE.TEXT: This is the list of all your programs
TOUR.LIBRARY.FAV.TEXT: You can mark programs as favorite, and you can sort and filter by favorites.
TOUR.LIBRARY.LABELS.TEXT: Add labels to a program to be able to filter by label. Our predefined function blocks already contain a label.
TOUR.LIBRARY.ACTIONS.TEXT: The default action is to edit the program. Use the dropdown menu to get all actions.
TOUR.LIBRARY.NEW_PROGRAM.TEXT: Use this button to create a new program.
TOUR.BUILDER.DESC: With the builder you can create robot programs via drag & drop.
TOUR.BUILDER.FNBS.DESC: All functions you need for your application. E.g. robot related blocks like "Move Cartesian" or control structures like "Condition".
TOUR.BUILDER.FNBS.FILTER.DESC: Filter function blocks by title or label.
TOUR.BUILDER.CONNECTIONS.TEXT: When you open connections of a skill, which has more than 3 connections, you'll only see variables' nodes without connections. Click on a node to build its connections.
TOUR.BUILDER.ADD_FNB.TEXT: Add blocks via drag&drop or use the "+" button.
TOUR.BUILDER.DATA_FLOW.TEXT: On the right side your program flow will be created.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.MANUAL_START: Visit the Trajectory Wizard inside the Builder to complete this.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.POSE.TEXT: Enter your pose coordinates and orientation here.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.WIZARD: Set pose using the Operator Panel
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.WIZARD.TEXT: Or you can open the Operator Panel to move the robot to your desired position.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.GOTO.TEXT: If you manually set a pose, you can use this button to move the robot to the position.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.TAKE_POSE.TEXT: Use this button to use the current pose.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.WAYPOINTS.TEXT: With this list you can create and edit multiple waypoints.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.DESC: For many predefined function blocks we have created so called wizards which will help you to set the correct parameters.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.WELCOME: Welcome to the drag&bot Operator Panel
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.MOVE.TEXT: Click and hold the arrow buttons to move the robot in this direction. You can also directly use the Interactive Markers inside the visualization.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.MARKERS.TEXT: Click here to hide or show the Interactive Markers in the visualization.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.MOVETO.TEXT: Use "Move to position" to fine-tune your coordinates.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.JOINTS.TEXT: You can also move the robot by controlling the joint angles.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.GRIPPER.TEXT: On this tab of the Operator Panel you can open or close the gripper.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.IO.TEXT: On this tab of the Operator Panel you can view and set I/Os.
TOUR.MOVE_TO_POSITION.VALUES.TEXT: Enter your target coordinates and orientation.
TOUR.MOVE_TO_POSITION.TAKE.TEXT: You can also take the current values and then adjust them.
TOUR.MOVE_TO_POSITION.BUTTON.TEXT: Click and hold this button to move to the target coordinates. If there is an error, the position might not be reachable.
TOUR.MOVE_TO_POSITION.REL_ABS.TEXT: Here you can switch between absolute movements and movements relative to the current position.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.WELCOME: Welcome to the drag&bot Operator Cockpit
TOUR.RUNVIEW.SELECT_PROGRAM.TEXT: In the top left corner you can select or change a program.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.CONTROLS.TEXT: Start, pause and stop your program or execute it stepwise.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.CONTROLS.SPEED.TEXT: Use the slider to adjust the speed of the robot.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.CONFIG_DASHBOARD.TEXT: Configure the dashboard panel sizes according to your needs.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.DASHBOARD.TEXT: The dashboard in the lower part contains context related content about your program, e.g. the program flow or the visualization.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.DASHBOARD.TEXT2: You can create and configure multiple dashboards.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.SELECT_DASHBOARD.TEXT: Switch between dashboards and create or edit dashboards.
TOUR.RUNVIEW.SELECT_DASHBOARD.TEXT.OPR: Switch between dashboards for different use cases.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.MANUAL_START: Open the edit mode of a Operator Cockpit dashboard to complete this.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.TITLE: Operator Cockpit configuration
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.DESC: In the edit mode you can adapt your dashboard to match your use case.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.ADD_PANEL.TEXT: Click the "+" button at the bottom to add a new widget.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.ADD_COL.TEXT: Click the "+" button on the right to add a new column.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.MOVE.TEXT: Use drag and drop to move widgets to a different position.
TOUR.RUNVIEW_EDITOR.RESIZE.TEXT: Use the resize handles to adapt the size of your widgets.
TOUR.CREATE_PROGRAM.START: In this tour you will learn how to create your first program.
TOUR.NEW_PROGRAM.DESC: Click the "New program" button to start a new program. You can also find this button on the home page.
TOUR.NEW_PROGRAM.LIBRARY.DESC: Open the program overview where you can find existing programs and create new ones.
TOUR.BUILDER.DATA_FLOW.TEXT2: You should now see the move block here.
TOUR.BUILDER.PARAMETRIZE.DESC: To define the movement open the parameter view.
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL_OVERLAY.INTRO.TEXT: Here you can open the operator panel
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL_OVERLAY.OPEN.TEXT: This allows you to access the most important functionalities of your robot system at any time
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.CHANGE_REF.TEXT: Here you can select from different reference coordinate systems in which the robot is moved
TOUR.OPERATOR_PANEL.TOGGLE_ARROWS.DESC: Here you can toggle the control-arrows to move the robot.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.RELATIVE_WAYPOINTS.TEX: Here you can switch to the full view where you can set an offset and a reference pose based on which an exact pose will be calculated.
TOUR.BUILDER.TRAJ.TOGGLE_WAYPOINTS.TEXT: Here you can switch between the detailed waypoint list and the view for editing individual waypoints.
